### ============================================
### OrioSearch API - REST Client Tests
### ============================================
### Requires VS Code extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client)
### Start the stack first: docker compose up --build

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiKey = your-secret-key-here


### ============================================
### Health & Info
### ============================================

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### OpenAPI Docs (Swagger)
GET {{baseUrl}}/docs

###

### LLM Tool Schema (OpenAI function-calling format)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tool-schema

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Basic
### ============================================

### Basic search (fast, snippets only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "python fastapi tutorial",
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Search with topic = news
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "artificial intelligence",
  "topic": "news",
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Search with time range filter
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "latest python release",
  "time_range": "week",
  "max_results": 3
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Advanced (with content extraction)
### ============================================

### Advanced search - fetches and extracts full page content
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "how to use docker compose",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Search with include_raw_content
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "redis caching best practices",
  "include_raw_content": true,
  "max_results": 3
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Images
### ============================================

### Search with images
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "cute cats",
  "include_images": true,
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Advanced search with images
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "machine learning architecture diagrams",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "include_images": true,
  "max_results": 3
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Domain Filters
### ============================================

### Include only specific domains
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "python async",
  "include_domains": ["docs.python.org", "realpython.com"],
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### Exclude specific domains
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "javascript frameworks 2025",
  "exclude_domains": ["medium.com", "w3schools.com"],
  "max_results": 5
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - Full featured
### ============================================

### Everything combined
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "self hosted search engine",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "topic": "general",
  "max_results": 5,
  "include_raw_content": true,
  "include_images": true,
  "exclude_domains": ["pinterest.com"],
  "time_range": "month"
}

###


### ============================================
### SEARCH - SSE Streaming
### ============================================

### Stream search results (Server-Sent Events)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/stream
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "query": "python async programming",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Stream advanced search with extraction
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/stream
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "query": "fastapi best practices",
  "search_depth": "advanced",
  "max_results": 3
}

###


### ============================================
### EXTRACT - Content extraction
### ============================================

### Extract single URL
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": ["https://example.com"]
}

###

### Extract multiple URLs (tests Redis pipeline batching)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html",
    "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/",
    "https://httpd.apache.org/"
  ],
  "format": "markdown"
}

###

### Extract with text format
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_scraping"
  ],
  "format": "text"
}

###

### Extract - test error handling (bad URL)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://example.com",
    "https://thisdomaindoesnotexist12345.com/page"
  ]
}

###


### ============================================
### AUTH - API Key Authentication
### ============================================
### (Enable auth in config.yaml first:
###   auth:
###     enabled: true
###     api_keys: ["your-secret-key-here"]
### )

### Search with API key (should succeed when auth enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}

{
  "query": "test auth",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Search without API key (should return 401 when auth enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test no auth",
  "max_results": 3
}

###

### Search with invalid API key (should return 403 when auth enabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer invalid-key-here

{
  "query": "test bad auth",
  "max_results": 3
}

###


### ============================================
### Edge cases & error handling
### ============================================

### Missing query field (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "max_results": 5
}

###

### max_results out of range (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "test",
  "max_results": 50
}

###

### Extract with no URLs (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": []
}

###

### Extract with too many URLs (should return 422, max 20)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extract
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "urls": [
    "https://example.com/1", "https://example.com/2", "https://example.com/3",
    "https://example.com/4", "https://example.com/5", "https://example.com/6",
    "https://example.com/7", "https://example.com/8", "https://example.com/9",
    "https://example.com/10", "https://example.com/11", "https://example.com/12",
    "https://example.com/13", "https://example.com/14", "https://example.com/15",
    "https://example.com/16", "https://example.com/17", "https://example.com/18",
    "https://example.com/19", "https://example.com/20", "https://example.com/21"
  ]
}

###


### ============================================
### Verify X-Request-ID header
### ============================================

### Check that response includes X-Request-ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "request id test",
  "max_results": 1
}

### Pass custom request ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/search
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-ID: my-custom-trace-id-123

{
  "query": "custom trace id test",
  "max_results": 1
}
